00:18:24.388 --> 00:18:27.000
But there's another point.

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:30.258
I told you how the structure of
DNA with the complimentary

00:18:30.258 --> 00:18:32.986
strands with
G pairing with C and A pairing

00:18:32.986 --> 00:18:35.231
with T immediately gave rise to
an

00:18:35.231 --> 00:18:38.963
insight as to how the genetic
material could be replicated.

00:18:38.963 --> 00:18:41.151
And
you guys know that it's held

00:18:41.151 --> 00:18:43.468
together by hydrogen bonds
between

00:18:43.468 --> 00:18:47.180
base pairs which are about
one-twentieth the strength of

00:18:47.180 --> 00:18:48.536
the
covalent bonds.

00:18:48.536 --> 00:18:51.703
So you're able to peel the
strands apart without

00:18:51.703 --> 00:18:53.375
breaking the covalent bonds.

00:18:53.375 --> 00:18:55.821
And then by pairing A with T
and G with

00:18:55.821 --> 00:18:59.940
C and doing that on both
strands then you can end up with

00:18:59.940 --> 00:19:01.520
two identical copies.

00:19:01.520 --> 00:19:05.680
And so if you do two identical
copies and you do it again you

00:19:05.680 --> 00:19:06.264
get eight.

00:19:06.264 --> 00:19:09.358
One of the things we've
