00:19:45.152 --> 00:19:48.902
that at the end you now have
two cells and you've got

00:19:48.902 --> 00:19:50.793
identical
copies of DNA.

00:19:50.793 --> 00:19:53.797
So if you're studying cancer,
for example,

00:19:53.797 --> 00:19:56.538
this
sort of thing is relevant to

00:19:56.538 --> 00:19:56.845
you.

00:19:56.845 --> 00:19:57.076
OK.

00:19:57.076 --> 00:20:00.721
So the issue of how --
Well, before I do that,

00:20:00.721 --> 00:20:01.470
