00:20:01.470 --> 00:20:04.165
Just a couple of things about
DNA

00:20:04.165 --> 00:20:06.712
replication before I dive into
this.

00:20:06.712 --> 00:20:09.332
So we all started out as a
single

00:20:09.332 --> 00:20:09.711
cell.

00:20:09.711 --> 00:20:14.498
I've got a lot more obviously
because I'm made up of a lot of

00:20:14.498 --> 00:20:14.928
cells.

00:20:14.928 --> 00:20:18.731
If I took all the DNA in my
body and I wind up all the

00:20:18.731 --> 00:20:21.629
molecules
in it, do you guys have any

00:20:21.629 --> 00:20:23.667
idea how long that would be?

00:20:23.667 --> 00:20:28.640
Who thinks it
would reach let's say across

00:20:28.640 --> 00:20:30.000
the room?

00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:30.375
OK.

00:20:30.375 --> 00:20:32.125
Across campus?

00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:34.250
Across Cambridge?

00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:36.375
Around the world?

00:20:36.375 --> 00:20:38.223
To
